
NPM Registery

1. To get the information of any package
    
url:registery.npmjs.org/underscore

2. To go directly to any package package

url: npm.im/underscore  





NPM Search

1. To Search info related to any package

> npm search keyword

keyword will be searched package and in package description
it is slow





NPM List

1. To list all packages installed in current project
>npm list 

2. To list all packages installed in current project in dev dependencies
>npm list --save-dev

3. To list all packages installed globally
>npm list -g


Pruning

1. To remove any package
Comparing the installed packages with package.json if not find then it will remove it from both
>npm prune

2. To remove any package
>npm prune express

3. To remove all dev dependencies
>npm prune --production





NPM Repo

1. To see oficial website of any package and view source code
>npm repo express




Upgrading NPM

1. To update the npm 
>npm i npm@latest -g 







NPM init

1.To make package.json file 
>npm init

2. To make package.json file with default options
>npm init -y





NPM Script

1.
>npm test
2.
>npm start

3. To run any Script
>npm run script-name






NPM Publishing packages
1.Create your account on npm

2.To add user
>npm adduser

3.

To publish package
1.Set up project in git
2.Create a package.json file
3. >npm publish

4.To get info about the published package
>npm info package-name

5. To update your package

1. Make changes to your code
2. change the version
3.Walk through the same publish process

6. To see npm version patch
>npm version patch

7. To show git tags in your published package
>git tag




Releasing an Alpha and Beta version

1. change the package.json file in version
"version":"1.3.0-beta.0"

2. 
>npm publish --tag beta

3. To install beta version
> npm i package @beta

